  "prompt": "Could Donald Trump be President?",
  "response": "As of the current information available, Donald Trump served as the 45th President of the United States from January 20, 2017, to January 20, 2021, after being defeated in the November 2020 election. According to the U.S. Constitution, specifically the 22nd Amendment, a person cannot be elected to the office of the President more than twice. Since Donald Trump has served only one term, he is theoretically eligible to run for and be elected to serve a second term in a future election. Whether he could become president again depends on various factors, including the political landscape, voter support, and success in any potential future campaign.",
